                            <comment id="12415364" author="narayanan" created="Thu, 8 Jun 2006 23:22:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find the patch attached for this issue. The patch required me to modify the getColumns query in  metadata.properties to return the autoincremented info and modify related tests that were failing as a result of this change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have changed all the tests that fail as a result of this change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The change will result in this additional column being produced irrespective of the jdk being run with. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will probably need a release note informing of this additional column to applications that use DatabaseMetaData.getColumns with a lower jdk verion other than mustang.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanx&lt;br/&gt;
Narayanan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415566" author="rhillegas" created="Sat, 10 Jun 2006 00:36:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m afraid that this patch breaks the upgrade test Upgrade_10_1_10_2. I&apos;m also afraid that I committed this patch at subversion revision 413084 before realizing that I hadn&apos;t actually checked the derbyall results. I merged the change out and reran the upgrade and metadata tests as a sanity check. I have backed out this patch at subversion revision 413086.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415658" author="narayanan" created="Sat, 10 Jun 2006 18:01:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank You for taking a look at the patch and also for running the tests on the same. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran the upgrade tests using the following command&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java org.apache.derbyTesting.functionTests.harness.RunTest upgradeTests/Upgrade_10_1_10_2.java&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;on both a freshworkspace and a workspace with my changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I got the same .out file that u get when the test fails in both the cases. i understood that the failures are the same for this test in both the cases. Also I inferred from this that this checkin had not introduced any additional failures to this test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also I found &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1375&quot; title=&quot;upgradeTests/Upgrade_10_1_10_2.java fails - master files need update?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1375&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1375&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; filed related to this issue. This has however been filed with platform specified as  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OS: Solaris 10 1/06 s10x_u1wos_19a X86 32bits - SunOS 5.10 Generic_118844-26&lt;br/&gt;
JVM: Sun Microsystems Inc. 1.5.0_04 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran the tests with 1.4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please guide me further in whether i have done any mistake while running the test. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanx&lt;br/&gt;
Narayanan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415675" author="narayanan" created="Sat, 10 Jun 2006 23:13:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry! My mistake. Saw the out files incorrectly. Will post the patch with the update cannon also.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanx and sorry once again for the redundant posts&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Narayanan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415838" author="narayanan" created="Mon, 12 Jun 2006 18:42:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch once again with the Upgrade cannon. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanx for the earlier reviews and comments&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanx&lt;br/&gt;
Narayanan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12415877" author="rhillegas" created="Tue, 13 Jun 2006 01:14:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the update, Narayanan. IS_AUTOCREMENT_v2.diff passes derbyall now, modulo the wisconsin noise. Committed at subversion revision 413710.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
